 families", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9926368594169617, "span": {"begin": 681, "end": 700}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013256"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "steroid", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9963687658309937, "span": {"begin": 712, "end": 719}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013256"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "steroid", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9984139204025269, "span": {"begin": 775, "end": 782}}, {"id": ["mesh:D000728"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "androgens", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9991451501846313, "span": {"begin": 830, "end": 839}}, {"id": ["mesh:D006058"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "malformation of reproductive organs", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999879002571106, "span": {"begin": 859, "end": 894}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013739"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "testosterone", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9973462820053101, "span": {"begin": 949, "end": 961}}, {"id": ["mesh:C032279"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "phthalates", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9989749193191528, "span": {"begin": 1036, "end": 1046}}], "text": "In this key event relationship we are focused on the decrease in activity of steroidogenesis genes involved in the synthesis of steroid compounds and corresponding decrease in testosterone levels.&nbsp; Steroidogenesis is the process of generating biological hormones starting from cholesterol as precursor to create a variety of steroid structures via enzyme catalyzed reactions.&nbsp; A large number of genes are involved in regulating steroidogenesis, so here we present evidence from available empirical studies. &nbsp;Decreased testosterone levels are most often noted as resulting from decreases in activities of enzymes&nbsp;in the StAR, Cyp11, Cyp17, p450, HSD3&beta;, and SR-B1 gene families within the steroid biosynthesis pathway, resulting in decreased precursor steroid compounds.  Decreased steroidogenesis rates of androgens has been linked to malformation of reproductive organs and decreased reproduction function through decreased testosterone levels&nbsp;(see Palermo et al. 2021 for review with focus on exposure to phthalates).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 16:11:38 +0000 2026"}